article.headline: California 66, Oregon State 57
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Leigh Gregory had a season-high 18 points
and eight rebounds as California beat Oregon State 66-57 on
Thursday.

Jacqueline Sanchez added eight points and 12 rebounds and Renee
Wright had nine points and eight rebounds for the Golden Bears
(11-15, 4-13).

Shannon Howell had 15 of her 17 points in the second half and
Hollye Chapman also had 17 points for the Beavers (14-12, 8-9
Pac-10).

California, with no starters over 6-foot-1, crushed the Beavers
on the boards, pulling down 19 offensive rebounds, and
outrebounding Oregon State 50-42.

Cal shot just 26 percent in the first half, but led 29-27 at
halftime as the Beavers had nine turnovers.

Oregon State led early, but the Bears went on an 8-0 run to take
the lead just before halftime.

The Bears opened up the second half on a 10-2 run and eventually
increased the lead to 49-38. With Cal leading 55-45, Howell scored
on a putback and then hit a turnaround jumper to cut the lead to
six points at 2:58.

But Gregory converted a quick basket for the Bears, and Oregon
State got no closer.

The Beavers finished the game with 18 turnovers.
